  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nAllow all contract developers (junior and senior) to get started with the optimal contract base avoiding common mistakes.\r\nIn the current ERC1155 design, the `name` and `symbol` is omitted (ERC721 has them passed via constructor).\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n\r\nChange https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC1155/ERC1155.sol\r\n\r\n```\r\n    // Used as the URI for all token types by relying on ID substitution, e.g. https://token-cdn-domain/{id}.json\r\n    string private _uri;\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev See {_setURI}.\r\n     */\r\n    constructor(string memory uri_) {\r\n        _setURI(uri_);\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nto \r\n\r\n```\r\n    // Contract name\r\n    string public name;\r\n\r\n    // Contract symbol\r\n    string public symbol;\r\n\r\n    // Used as the URI for all token types by relying on ID substitution, e.g. https://token-cdn-domain/{id}.json\r\n    string private _uri;\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev See {_setURI}.\r\n     */\r\n    constructor(string name_, string, symbol_, string memory uri_) {\r\n       name = name_;\r\n       symbol = symbol_;\r\n        _setURI(uri_);\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nor set them privately and add some `view` methods \r\n<!-- Make sure that you have reviewed the OpenZeppelin Contracts Contributor Guidelines. -->\r\n<!-- https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md -->\r\n",
